 in a sealable container.","To make your own vanilla bean paste, refer to the recipe on Cookidoo (www.cookidoo.com.au).","Be sure to use only food-grade peppermint oil in this recipe. You can find it at most baking supply stores or online.","We used silicone ice cream moulds (available at TheMix Shop - www.thermomix.com.au\/shop or www.thermomix.co.nz\/shop) to create 6 popsicles. However, the number of popsicles you make will depend on the size of your moulds.","Store any leftover chocolate in a sealable container in the refrigerator. Warm (to a liquid state) before serving.","If you don't want to make popsicles, you can scoop ice cream into bowls. Simply remove from freezer 5-10 minutes before serving to soften slightly."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","4h 15m","6 portions"]}